# Guru99 Banking Website Test Automation

This project contains automated and manual test cases for the Guru99 Demo Banking website.

Website under test:
https://demo.guru99.com/V1/index.php

The automation focuses on real banking workflows such as:

- Login
- Create New Customer
- Edit Customer
- Delete Customer
- Create New Account
- Edit Account
- Delete Account
- Balance Enquiry
- Mini Statement
- Fund Transfer
- Customised Statement
- Logout

The tests are written in Python using Selenium WebDriver.

---

## Technologies Used

- Python 3
- Selenium WebDriver
- WebDriver Manager
- PyTest
- Pandas
- OpenPyXL

---

## Project Structure

project/

├── test/               # Test scripts  
├── pages/              # Page Object classes  
├── data/               # Test data files (Excel)  
├── reports/            # Test reports  
├── requirements.txt  
└── README.md  

---

## Setup Instructions

1) Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Mudit-018/Guru99-Banking-Test-Automation.git  
cd Guru99-Banking-Test-Automation  

2) Create and activate virtual environment:

python -m venv .venv  
Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass  
.\.venv\Scripts\activate  

3) Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt  

---

## Test Credentials

To run the tests you must generate valid login credentials from the Guru99 demo site:

https://demo.guru99.com/V1/index.php

Use the "Generate Access" option on the website to get:

- User ID  
- Password  

Update the credentials inside the test files before running.

---

## Run Tests

From the project root folder:

pytest  

or run individual test files:

python test/be_testsuite.py  

---

## Notes

- This is a demo automation project created for learning and portfolio purposes.
- The Guru99 site resets data frequently, so some tests may fail if records already exist.
- Credentials must be updated regularly.

